Change: Redesigned the 4 role-dashboard metric cards (Top business/shop/employee, Most-sold product) from a screenshot showing them as small boxes with a huge empty area below on wide screens. Per follow-up feedback, arranged as a 2x2 grid (2 top, 2 bottom) instead of 4-in-a-row, each card much larger with a full (non-sparkline) Recharts area chart inside instead of the old tiny 76px compact sparkline.
Implementation: `BaselineDashboards.tsx`'s `MetricCell` now renders a `.dashboard-metric-header` (label/entity name/value) followed by a `.dashboard-metric-chart` wrapper containing the full (non-`compact`) `AuthorizedLineChart`, with a proper `valueFormatter` (currency via `formatMoney`, or "N sold" via the existing `scopedEntityReport.unitsSold` i18n key — this also fixed a pre-existing hardcoded "sold" string in the same function) and a new `emptyLabel` (reusing the existing `roleDashboard.drill.graphEmpty` key) so an entity with zero chart points shows an intentional "No sales data to visualize yet" placeholder instead of a mysterious blank rectangle. `AuthorizedLineChart.tsx` gained the `emptyLabel` prop and now renders that placeholder whenever its data array is empty. `MasterDashboard.css`: `.dashboard-leader-grid` switched from `repeat(4, minmax(0,1fr))` to `repeat(2, minmax(0,1fr))` (2x2 for the master/business dashboards' 4 metrics; shop's 3 metrics wrap 2+1; cashier's 2 metrics fill one row) with `align-items: stretch`; `.dashboard-metric-link` became a flex column with `min-height: 380px` and larger entity-name typography (30px); `.dashboard-metric-chart` is `flex:1; min-height:240px` so the chart fills the remaining card height, with a scoped `.dashboard-metric-chart .authorized-chart { height: 100% }` override (kept local to this file, doesn't touch the shared `.authorized-chart` base rule used by `ReportsPage`/`EntityReportDetailPage`). Removed the now-redundant `@media (max-width: 1020px)` `.dashboard-leader-grid` override (it set the same 2-column value that's now the default); the existing `@media (max-width: 760px)` rule still collapses to a single column on mobile.
